fs of how taunt works.  Other than wanting to test it myself, I'm not real sure how to respond other than to say that yesterday was an incredibly buggy day.  I know I have felt at times like taunt wasn't working right, but I don't think I've ever had it not work 77 times in a row.  And about people saying that pallies being considered better on all levels by all other classes (btw thanks for the defense in this regard, I'm not trying to preach my argument as much as get a bit of intelligent discussion going instead of a rant that should be in the tavern forum), you are off your rocker.  Warriors always have been and always will be in equal (or greater) demand than pallies and SKs have, and I see no reason for that to change.  All I see in this thread is people announcing all the quite obvious strengths of a paladin, and not mentioning the quite obvious strengths of warriors.  I'm here to participate in intelligent discussion, not to watch a thread dissolve into single-sided statements and hollow insults. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=193009"> Grendon's Stuff </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
