<br>
Completely on target. In a raid situation, warriors are giving some quality time with the mob to themselves to get un-friendly. In an experience group where the mobs life expectancy is 100 seconds, spending 10-20 seconds building aggro every fight means you're gimping the groups experience. Take a look at the cleric boards, there's a thread about knights vs warriors as exp tanks, pallys are hands down favorites.<br>
<br>
One thing that I've found to help some (when playing my cleric) is to cast Tarnations (8 sec stun-knockback) on incomming. What this does is either a) stun the mob and give the warrior 2 taunt key pressings to gain a decent lead over the slower or b) resists stun and comes over to smack the cleric <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
In either of those cases I (as a cleric) can either DA/DB, run around in circles screaming &quot;GET IT OFF&quot;, root the mob, or if the war has AE taunt he uses it at this point. At level 64 my cleric has about a 10% resist rate on stun, and even then, if the war is on his toes, he'll usually be able to taunt fast enough to grab aggro back before the mob reaches me.<br>
<br>
Why go through this hastle? Because it's faster than letting the war solo for a CH worth of damage. Also it's mana efficient for the cleric, within the 8 seconds of the stun the slower usually does his thing. I've found that once the mob's slowed, I can get away with 1 CH per fight on the war in PoV, 2 in BoT/HoH.<br>
<br>
Looking at the mana efficiency-<br>
Ch=400 mana<br>
Stun= 325 mana<br>
Supernal Remedy= 400 mana<br>
<br>
So, it's much better to stun once, CH once per fight than CH tank, SR enchanter, SR self, CH tank again, SR tank before next mob.<br>
<br>
The key is to give warriors some kind of aggro to taunt with.. hitting taunt at the begining of the fight otherwise is just a waste.<br>
<br>
Jaxga Ironash - 64 cleric<br>
Zebedii Ironash- 63 war<br>
