<br>
If someone doctors said coin, and cheats when they &quot;flip&quot; it by timing the flip with skill and timing, they most certainly COULD make it come up heads 77 times in a row....<br>
(You know that experienced hybrids actually TIME their sword swings and their taunt spells so as to land to give them maximum Taunt AFTER a taunt skill press, right?<br>
Example: Cast Terror, wait until right before it lands, press taunt.... terror lands, SK is 600points ahead of the highest person period.  SK with the highest experience will time sword swings for 300+ to land just after the Taunt and Terror, making for 1100-1200pt hatred buffers...)<br>
<br>
<br>
TAUNT itself seems fine...  what warriors actually need is a method to control some numerical taunt value. (TAUNT skill places you on top and is POSITIONAL hate)<br>
A warrior who is able to press a button to add some numerical hate on TOP of their 1st place positional advantage would have a LOT easier time holding aggro.<br>
<br>
I suggest adding a simple option....<br>
<br>
Warriors gain a new skill at 30th,<br>
LOW BLOW<br>
-Greys KICK, SLAM, and BASH and is on the same timer.<br>
-Does KICK damage, (no stun, doesn't push)<br>
-Adds +100 in hate (in addition to the hate caused by the damage) the result would be (between damage-hate and direct-hate) a numerical hate addition on the level of 1/6 - 1/4 of Enraging blow.<br>
-The LOW BLOW can MISS, but it still does its numerical hate addition (the damage-hate of course doesn't make it)<br>
<br>
The Warrior is effectively trying to kick their opponenet in the jimmy....  the opponent is gonna notice said attack and take exception to the warrior.<br>
<br>
Warriors would remain lower than Knights in hatred production,  yet the CONTROL of hatred and the fact that the +100 hate is both unresistable, and unlimited (except by refresh), means the warrior should be able to hold aggro better than now.<br>
This of course means that some warriors will have to study up a tad...<br>
TIME your swings and your TAUNT button so that it happens in the following order,<br>
TAUNT, (immediately after) SWING, LOW BLOW.<br>
The warrior (if Taunt is successful) would be their weapon swings AND at least 100 hate over the next highest hated player.<br>
<br>
Now, let me restate... I agree that warriors could use a little more hatred generation control...<br>
but it is PRECISION and TIMING that will make that happen.... not brute &quot;generate 8MILLION, work EVERY TIME, skills that would trivialize hybrids and make warriors the only tank again.&quot;<br>
 <br>
Warriors should NEVER taunt at distance like a Hybrid.<br>
SPELLS are what allow us to taunt at distance...  when warriors sling spells at will, what is the point of being a hybrid?  When Warriors exceed Hybrid Taunt, what use is there for Knights?<br>
<br>
Hybrids should be better at hatred... they represent varying radical alignments...  especially Paladins and Shadowknights.<br>
