So, here's the deal.... I stood next to a mob who was being killed. I sat there and hit the taunt button. Did nothing else to generate aggro, no attack on no ranged attacks, no nothing, just press taunt.<br>
END QUOTE<br>
<br>
Your test is flawed due to your lack of understanding how th GAME works, let alone the medium you are playing on. Of course the test turned out with terrible results.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Actually, YOU are the one who's shown that you neither read entire threads (where I made it pretty clear that I didn't consider this to be definitive), nor have an understanding how taunt works.    <br>
<br>
let me explain something to you.   The 3 times that it worked, I was beaten on for almost 30 seconds.    <br>
<br>
What can we infer with this?  It's likely that we can infer that someone at a range had a fairly high position on the aggro list, yet the mob didn't bother chasing them and was still beating on someone within proximity, because NO ONE changed behaviours ecept the mob.  No one stopped attacking, no one did anything different out of the 40ish people who were there, yet with a single taunt I had the mob's attention for approximately 30 seconds, doing *zilch* to generate additional aggro.    <br>
<br>
You, Mr. &quot;I'll educate people&quot; are doing a piss poor job at it.   While I agree that if I took over the top melee person's position and he then contributed additional hate which removed me fom the top of the list prior to the next round of attacks, I'd have not been hit.   This happens from time to time even in places like Sanctus Seru, where there's a definitive message and yet even post taunt, you dont' have aggro.   I knw full well how this works, but there's a crucial difference.   In almost every instance, the mob will physically turn and look at you for a small amount of time, then turn back.   This did *not* happen.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
QUOTE<br>
After doing it 77 times in a row, with no attention from the mob, I was wondering exactly what was the problem. I wondered if those mobs wee simply taunt immune, or if the way we all thought about taunt was wrong.... on the 78th time, it worked. On the 81st time, it worked.... on the 92nd time, it worked. This meant that.... the mobs WERENT immune, and that it DID work the way we all thought it did (auto to top of hate list) but that the rate of it working was stupidly low.<br>
END QUOTE<br>
<br>
So for &quot;X&quot; amount of time you hit taunt at the wrong timing and you are telling us that WARRIOR taunt sucks because you are getting your taunt stolen due to no other numerical hate adding in. On the 78th time, you actually got lucky in your timing... likely someone took a bathroom break... I am sorry, but you are blowing this out of proportion because you do not understand what you are doing. You are failing due to your lack of knowledge...<br>
<br>
Taunt puts you on top of the list... with a lower skillcap than you have and without casting a single spell or swinging ONCE I can taunt off mobs from elemental planes. (did it last night) Taunt is a powerful tool, but alone it is currently not what it needs to be for warriors.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
As can anyone, but... this is crucial... *if it works*.     You have no clue as to my lack of knowledge, you make several assumptions that I did or didn't do &quot;x, y, or z&quot;, when in fact you have no clue whether I did or not.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>QUOTE<br>
Before you say &quot;gee, there had to be a string of bad luck... let's say for the sake of argument that taunt is 50% reliable.... Go flip a quarter, you have a 50% chance of heads or tails... flip it 77 times in a row, and tell me if you get heads each time. The odds of this happenning are so low that a number cannot be made to represent this possibility. You have a higher chance of being struck by lightning on a clear day while indoors.<br>
END QUOTE<br>
<br>
If someone doctors said coin, and cheats when they &quot;flip&quot; it by timing the flip with skill and timing, they most certainly COULD make it come up heads 77 times in a row....<br>
(You know that experienced hybrids actually TIME their sword swings and their taunt spells so as to land to give them maximum Taunt AFTER a taunt skill press, right?<br>
Example: Cast Terror, wait until right before it lands, press taunt.... terror lands, SK is 600points ahead of the highest person period. SK with the highest experience will time sword swings for 300+ to land just after the Taunt and Terror, making for 1100-1200pt hatred buffers...)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Timing spells casts between slow, known delay factor swings is uhh....entirely irrelevant to this, and.... a warrior who was NOT pressing taunt was the recipient of the aggro in my example.    Try again.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>TAUNT itself seems fine... what warriors actually need is a method to control some numerical taunt value. (TAUNT skill places you on top and is POSITIONAL hate)<br>
A warrior who is able to press a button to add some numerical hate on TOP of their 1st place positional advantage would have a LOT easier time holding aggro.<br>
<br>
I suggest adding a simple option....<br>
<br>
Warriors gain a new skill at 30th,<br>
LOW BLOW<br>
-Greys KICK, SLAM, and BASH and is on the same timer.<br>
-Does KICK damage, (no stun, doesn't push)<br>
-Adds +100 in hate (in addition to the hate caused by the damage) the result would be (between damage-hate and direct-hate) a numerical hate addition on the level of 1/6 - 1/4 of Enraging blow.<br>
-The LOW BLOW can MISS, but it still does its numerical hate addition (the damage-hate of course doesn't make it)<br>
<br>
The Warrior is effectively trying to kick their opponenet in the jimmy.... the opponent is gonna notice said attack and take exception to the warrior.<br>
<br>
Warriors would remain lower than Knights in hatred production, yet the CONTROL of hatred and the fact that the +100 hate is both unresistable, and unlimited (except by refresh), means the warrior should be able to hold aggro better than now.<br>
This of course means that some warriors will have to study up a tad...<br>
TIME your swings and your TAUNT button so that it happens in the following order,<br>
TAUNT, (immediately after) SWING, LOW BLOW.<br>
The warrior (if Taunt is successful) would be their weapon swings AND at least 100 hate over the next highest hated player.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't disagree with your assessment of needs.   <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Now, let me restate... I agree that warriors could use a little more hatred generation control...<br>
but it is PRECISION and TIMING that will make that happen.... not brute &quot;generate 8MILLION, work EVERY TIME, skills that would trivialize hybrids and make warriors the only tank again.&quot;<br>
<br>
Warriors should NEVER taunt at distance like a Hybrid.<br>
SPELLS are what allow us to taunt at distance... when warriors sling spells at will, what is the point of being a hybrid? When Warriors exceed Hybrid Taunt, what use is there for Knights?<br>
<br>
Hybrids should be better at hatred... they represent varying radical alignments... especially Paladins and Shadowknights.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
